  "The visceral pericardium (epicardium) is the inner layer of the pericardial sac that directly adheres to the surface of the heart. Visceral means it is attached to the organ itself, as opposed to parietal, which lines the body wall.": "心心肌外皮过膜()是心肌外心肌囊的内层,直接附在心脏的表面。子宫内皮意味着它附在器官本身上,而不是附在身体壁的皮质上。",
