  "Carpal region": "喀帕尔州",
  "The antecubital fossa (front of the elbow) is the standard anatomical site for venipuncture because the median cubital vein is superficial and accessible here. Healthcare workers must know this region by its anatomical name for accurate documentation.": "动脉前部(肘部前部)是输血的标准解剖场所,因为这里的颈部中位静脉是表面的,可以进入。 保健工作者必须用解剖名称了解这个区域以获取准确的文件。",
  "A surgeon is performing an operation on the heart and must cut through the membrane directly covering the heart's surface. This membrane is the:": "外科医生正在心脏上做手术,必须切穿直覆盖心脏表面的膜。",
  "Visceral peritoneum": "子宫腹膜",
  "Parietal peritoneum": "Parietal 近皮内膜",
  "Visceral pericardium (epicardium)": "子宫外心肌()",
  "Parietal pleura": "等质胸膜",
  "The visceral pericardium (also called the epicardium) is the serous membrane that directly adheres to the heart's surface. The parietal pericardium lines the outer fibrous sac, and between them is a small amount of serous fluid that reduces friction during heartbeats.": "心肌外心肌梗塞(又称心电图)是直接附在心脏表面的坚固膜。 皮肤外心肌膜线是外纤维囊,中间是少量的静脉液,可以减少心跳期间的摩擦。",
  "A medical student examining a patient notes that injury to the right arm has caused weakness in the right leg as well. The instructor explains that the arm and leg are on the same side, making them _____ structures.": "一名医科学生在检查病人时指出,右臂受伤也造成右腿虚弱。 教官解释说,右臂和腿是同一边的,使右臂结构成为____。",
  "Bilateral": "双边 双边",
  "Ipsilateral": "边边边",
  "Medial": "中介面l",
  "Contralateral": "反反",
  "The right arm and right leg are ipsilateral because they are on the same side of the body. If the injury affected the right arm and the left leg, those structures would be contralateral (on opposite sides).": "右臂和右腿是附带的,因为它们在身体的同一侧,如果受伤影响到右臂和左腿,这些结构将是反面的(对立的)。",
  "A patient complains of pain in the sole of their right foot after stepping on a nail. The nurse documents the injury location as the _____ surface of the right foot.": "一名病人在踩到钉子后抱怨右脚底部疼痛,护士记录受伤地点为右脚的 表面。",
  "Dorsal": "多索拉尔",
  "Plantar": "Plantar 计划计划",
  "Palmar": "棕榈",
